  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Unauthorised-Access"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Unauthorised Access"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Cases-of-Unauthorised-Access",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Cases of Unauthorised Access",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It can occur due to the following:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Poor authentication",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Poor access control\/authorisation",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Poor understanding of privacy policies.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Authentication",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Authentication",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Authentication is the process of verifying the identity of a user. It requires the user to prove their identity by",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "providing evidence from one or more of the following categories:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Something the user knows (password)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Something the user owns (mobile phone)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Something the user is (thumbprint)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Each category of evidence used for authentication is called an authentication factor",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "tabs" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Passwords are the most common form of authentication. Some passwords are entered together with a username that",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "identifies who the user claims to be.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "They can be a poor form of authentication if they are chosen poorly or not well-kept as a secret. Avoid using",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "birthdates, surnames and other things that can be easily guessed.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Use hard to guess passwords that are a mixture of lowercase, uppercase letters, numbers and symbols.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Avoid re-using passwords or leaving them unchanged for a long time as it makes it easier for an intruder to guess",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "the password. Use unique passwords for each computer and account, and update them at least once every 90 days.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "Knows: Passwords"
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Some authentication systems require evidence from more than 1 authentication factor. Banks typically issue a device",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "called a security token to users who wish to access their accounts online.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "A ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "security token",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is a device used specifically for authentication purposes, such as mobile phones and one-time",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "passwords (OTPs).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The type of authentication that uses evidence from both something a user knows and owns is called ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "2-factor authentication",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ".",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "2FA is stronger than a singular password as it is more difficult for an intruder to both guess a password and steal",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "the user’s security token. Hence, it is important to keep the security token in a secure location at all times and to",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "report a missing security token as soon as possible.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "If an OTP is sent wirelessly to a user’s mobile phone, it may be intercepted and used by an intruder during the",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "transmission process. If the secret algorithm used to generate OTPs is poorly chosen or accidentally revealed, an",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "intruder may find out how to generate OTPs without needing the security token at all.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "There is not much a user can do about this type of intrusion attempt.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "Owns: Security Tokens"
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "Biometrics",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is a type of authentication that is based on the measurement of human physical characteristics.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "For example, biometrics is used to identify a user by fingerprint or voice. Other characteristics used include the face,",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "iris, retina, and DNA.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The use of biometric identification is more secure as the physical characteristics measured are typically unique to the",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "individual and cannot be easily replicated. Thus, it helps prevent attempts to establish fraudulent identities and identity theft.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "However, biometric identification cannot be changed and is permenantly compromised if the biometric data is stolen.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Identity theft is the impersonation of another person to steal personal details such as name and identity number for fraudulent purposes.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "Is: Biometrics"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "tabNavigator"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
